today on the I-5--

1021
01:04:46,282 --> 01:04:50,452
Intense high-frequency bursts;
always at night.

1022
01:04:50,454 --> 01:04:54,356
Don't you receive your images,
your voices, at 3:00 a.m.?

1023
01:04:54,358 --> 01:04:55,824
It fits!

1024
01:04:55,826 --> 01:04:58,426
You're not crazy.

1025
01:04:58,428 --> 01:05:01,396
I never thought I was.

1026
01:05:01,398 --> 01:05:03,298
You and Phil were
talking that it could be

1027
01:05:03,300 --> 01:05:04,432
a satellite
orbiting Earth.

1028
01:05:04,434 --> 01:05:06,167
Right?

1029
01:05:06,169 --> 01:05:07,435
I remember you
saying that.

1030
01:05:07,437 --> 01:05:09,304
That was months ago.

1031
01:05:09,306 --> 01:05:11,373
You know how I am
with theories.

1032
01:05:11,375 --> 01:05:14,409
Like planes landing at LAX,
a new one every few minutes.

1033
01:05:14,411 --> 01:05:16,444
Our latest theory is that the
messages come from a parallel

1034
01:05:16,446 --> 01:05:19,381
universe.
Who cares about
your theories?

1035
01:05:19,383 --> 01:05:22,450
This is real.

1036
01:05:28,492 --> 01:05:31,259
♪ Every day
the satellite ♪

1037
01:05:31,261 --> 01:05:37,766
♪ Seems to be the door
at someone's reach ♪

1038
01:05:37,768 --> 01:05:39,567
For years, Nick
had placed his faith

1039
01:05:39,569 --> 01:05:42,470
in the instructions
of VALIS.

1040
01:05:42,472 --> 01:05:47,208
Moving to LA, going to work
for Progressive Records.

1041
01:05:47,210 --> 01:05:49,344
He thought of VALIS
as all-knowing,

1042
01:05:49,346 --> 01:05:52,180
a manifestation
of God's will.

1043
01:05:52,182 --> 01:05:56,451
If VALIS was just a satellite,
it reduced something limitless

1044
01:05:56,453 --> 01:06:00,055
to a finite reality,
a mere machine.

1045
01:06:00,057 --> 01:06:02,424
♪ Every day
the satellite... ♪♪

1046
01:06:16,539 --> 01:06:19,274
Breathe deeply.

1047
01:06:49,472 --> 01:06:52,240
Did you think we
would forsake you?

1048
01:06:52,242 --> 01:06:54,509
Is your belief
so weak?

1049
01:06:54,511 --> 01:06:56,077
Where am I?

1050
01:06:56,079 --> 01:06:57,512
A place above the stars.

1051
01:06:57,514 --> 01:07:01,082
This is where you
were truly born.

1052
01:07:01,084 --> 01:07:02,617
I come from
above the stars?

1053
01:07:02,619 --> 01:07:04,519
Many times.

1054
01:07:04,521 --> 01:07:07,555
Only now are you remembering
who you really are.

1055
01:07:07,557 --> 01:07:09,090
Who am I?

1056
01:07:09,092 --> 01:07:10,558
Everyone.

1057
01:07:10,560 --> 01:07:12,260
And all things.

1058
01:07:12,262 --> 01:07:14,496
You asked to be broken
down and healed.

1059
01:07:14,498 --> 01:07:17,565
This is that breaking
down and healing.

1060
01:07:17,567 --> 01:07:20,568
Soon you shall be
with us for all time.

1061
01:07:20,570 --> 01:07:23,638
I'm not going to die?
I won't cease to exist?

1062
01:07:23,640 --> 01:07:27,609
No one truly dies
and nothing is ever lost.

1063
01:07:27,611 --> 01:07:30,178
There is nowhere
for anything to go.

1064
01:07:30,180 --> 01:07:34,516
There is only here
and now, for all time.

1065
01:07:34,518 --> 01:07:39,220
Now that you have remembered,
there can be no forgetting.

1066
01:07:39,222 --> 01:07:41,089
Nick.

1067
01:07:41,091 --> 01:07:45,427
You are a lucky man.

1068
01:07:45,429 --> 01:07:47,429
I don't feel so lucky.

1069
01:07:47,431 --> 01:07:49,397
I've got the world's worst
headache in the world.

1070
01:07:49,399 --> 01:07:51,466
I'm not surprised,
you've been through a lot.

1071
01:07:51,468 --> 01:07:54,402
Let's take a look.

1072
01:07:54,404 --> 01:07:57,672
The steering wheel did
most of the damage.

1073
01:07:57,674 --> 01:08:00,408
I'm afraid you're going
to be with us for a while.

1074
01:08:00,410 --> 01:08:02,577
This kind of trauma...

1075
01:08:02,579 --> 01:08:04,479
What the--?

1076
01:08:04,481 --> 01:08:06,214
Is something wrong?

1077
01:08:06,216 --> 01:08:07,649
Just a minute.

1078
01:08:07,651 --> 01:08:11,419
Wow, your skin's hot.

1079
01:08:13,589 --> 01:08:15,490
Is this tender?

1080
01:08:15,492 --> 01:08:18,126
No.

1081
01:08:21,464 --> 01:08:27,635
Look, I'm glad you're all
right, but how is it possible?

1082
01:08:27,637 --> 01:08:30,472
The satellite
healed me.

1083
01:08:34,577 --> 01:08:38,113
There's something else
I've got to tell you.

1084
01:08:38,115 --> 01:08:41,282
The new secretary
at work, Sylvia.

1085
01:08:41,284 --> 01:08:44,319
She's part of
all this, too.

1086
01:08:44,321 --> 01:08:46,688
Are you sure you
can trust her?

1087
01:08:46,690 --> 01:08:49,324
I don't know,
I think so.

1088
01:08:49,326 --> 01:08:51,626
I'm still just
finding my way here.

1089
01:08:51,628 --> 01:08:55,363
There's no real chance of
overthrowing Fremont, is there?

1090
01:08:55,365 --> 01:08:57,332
Probably not.

1091
01:08:57,334 --> 01:08:58,700
But it's still
worth trying.

1092
01:08:58,702 --> 01:09:00,335
Yeah.

1093
01:09:00,337 --> 01:09:02,437
And what if it
ruins our lives?

1094
01:09:02,439 --> 01:09:04,739
And our son's life?

1095
01:09:04,741 --> 01:09:08,676
My friendship with Phil,
writer of pulp science fiction

1096
01:09:08,678 --> 01:09:12,480
stories is a false lead.

1097
01:09:12,482 --> 01:09:14,315
The authorities are looking for
something subversive to show up

1098
01:09:14,317 --> 01:09:16,317
in his books.

1099
01:09:16,319 --> 01:09:18,186
But the fact is we have a
better chance to get a message

1100
01:09:18,188 --> 01:09:20,321
out in a song.

1101
01:09:20,323 --> 01:09:23,758
If we're caught they'll
put us in prison or kill us,

1102
01:09:23,760 --> 01:09:26,494
so I'm making this videotape
for you, Ezra,

1103
01:09:26,496 --> 01:09:29,397
so that one day, you'll
know the truth....

1104
01:09:30,699 --> 01:09:32,133
Mr. Brady.

1105
01:09:32,135 --> 01:09:33,535
Is something wrong?

1106
01:09:33,537 --> 01:09:35,336
I know about
your mother.

1107
01:09:35,338 --> 01:09:37,739
What do you mean? What are
you doing here so late?

1108
01:09:37,741 --> 01:09:41,709
I know she was a recruiter for
the Communist Party and I know

1109
01:09:41,711 --> 01:09:45,313
she signed up
Richard Fremont.

1110
01:09:45,315 --> 01:09:46,414
I heard about your
car crash.

1111
01:09:46,416 --> 01:09:47,749
Are you all right?

1112
01:09:47,751 --> 01:09:49,684
You're talking
crazy right now.

1113
01:09:49,686 --> 01:09:51,653
Fremont and the Party think
their secret is safe.

1114
01:09:51,655 --> 01:09:55,657
But as a little girl, you must
have overheard conversations.

1115
01:09:55,659 --> 01:09:57,392
You're the only person
outside the highest ranks

1116
01:09:57,394 --> 01:09:59,194
of the Party who knows.

1117
01:09:59,196 --> 01:10:01,229
That's why the government
tried to kill you with cancer,

1118
01:10:01,231 --> 01:10:02,530
isn't it?
Why on earth would the
government want to harm me?

1119
01:10:02,532 --> 01:10:03,731
I'm nobody.

1120
01:10:03,733 --> 01:10:06,668
We're supposed to
work together.

1121
01:10:06,670 --> 01:10:10,171
Fremont's secret will go
out as a song in the form

1122
01:10:10,173 --> 01:10:11,673
of a subliminal message.

1123
01:10:11,675 --> 01:10:14,242
I'll make sure that it saturates
the airwaves before the

1124
01:10:14,244 --> 01:10:15,710
authorities get wise--
Listen to me.

1125
01:10:15,712 --> 01:10:16,711
My mother has been a
down-to-earth Republican

1126
01:10:16,713 --> 01:10:18,780
all her life.

1127
01:10:18,782 --> 01:10:20,615
She's just an ordinary woman
saddled with the name

1128
01:10:20,617 --> 01:10:22,650
"Aramchek."

1129
01:10:22,652 --> 01:10:24,652
The police have investigated her
over and over because of it

1130
01:10:24,654 --> 01:10:26,721
and it's lunatic stuff like
this that gets innocent people

1131
01:10:26,723 --> 01:10:29,657
into trouble.

1132
01:10:35,698 --> 01:10:38,700
Your friend
Silvia called.

1133
01:10:38,702 --> 01:10:41,769
What did she say?

1134
01:10:41,771 --> 01:10:43,705
She's at
the La Paz Bar.

1135
01:10:43,707 --> 01:10:46,407
She wants you to
meet her there.

1136
01:11:11,267 --> 01:11:13,434
I'm sorry if what I said before
offended you, I didn't--

1137
01:11:13,436 --> 01:11:14,736
No, it's okay.

1138
01:11:14,738 --> 01:11:17,772
I had now idea how
I was supposed to react.

1139
01:11:17,774 --> 01:11:20,708
I think
I'm being watched.

1140
01:11:20,710 --> 01:11:24,712
I've received a new transmission
since I last saw you

1141
01:11:24,714 --> 01:11:27,548
and I'm to initiate you further
into the organization by--

1142
01:11:27,550 --> 01:11:28,716
Org--

1143
01:11:28,718 --> 01:11:31,586
Organization?

1144
01:11:31,588 --> 01:11:33,588
Aramchek.

1145
01:11:33,590 --> 01:11:35,590
Aramchek really exists?

1146
01:11:35,592 --> 01:11:37,558
Sure.

1147
01:11:37,560 --> 01:11:39,460
Why would Fremont waste
his time trying to stamp out

1148
01:11:39,462 --> 01:11:41,296
an imaginary group?

1149
01:11:41,298 --> 01:11:45,600
So what I said about
your mother is true?

1150
01:11:45,602 --> 01:11:48,569
Basically, yeah.

1151
01:11:48,571 --> 01:11:50,605
So what is Aramchek?

1152
01:11:50,607 --> 01:11:52,740
It's the people contacted by
the satellite, which in turn

1153
01:11:52,742 --> 01:11:57,278
receives instructions from a
star system called Albemuth.

1154
01:11:57,280 --> 01:12:00,315
Life on this planet came
from there originally.

1155
01:12:00,317 --> 01:12:02,784
So whenever we fall into
overwhelming difficulties,

1156
01:12:02,786 --> 01:12:07,588
the satellite serves as our
link back to Albemuth.

1157
01:12:07,590 --> 01:12:10,425
I think I intuited
most of this already.

1158
01:12:10,427 --> 01:12:12,827
Yeah, Aramchek includes
hundreds, maybe thousands

1159
01:12:12,829 --> 01:12:17,632
of people, mostly here and in
the former Soviet Union.

1160
01:12:17,634 --> 01:12:19,133
We're each contacted
individually, so only

1161
01:12:19,135 --> 01:12:21,502
the satellite knows
who, and how many,

1162
01:12:21,504 --> 01:12:25,473
where and exactly what
we're supposed to do.

1163
01:12:25,475 --> 01:12:26,641
Last call.

1164
01:12:26,643 --> 01:12:27,742
What would you like?

1165
01:12:27,744 --> 01:12:30,278
Something strong.

1166
01:12:30,280 --> 01:12:33,815
But I guess I'll
settle for club soda.

1167
01:12:33,817 --> 01:12:35,516
Make that two.

1168
01:12:35,518 --> 01:12:38,519
Thanks.

1169
01:12:38,521 --> 01:12:41,689
VALIS has done it before,
in the time of Jesus

1170
01:12:41,691 --> 01:12:44,058
and the early
Christians.

1171
01:12:44,060 --> 01:12:46,661
It didn't quite
work out then.

1172
01:12:46,663 --> 01:12:50,498
I always thought I made up
that word, VALIS.

1173
01:12:50,500 --> 01:12:53,067
That word was
placed in your mind.

1174
01:12:53,069 --> 01:12:57,805
VALIS is how we all refer to it
while we assimilate the shock.
Shock?

1175
01:12:57,807 --> 01:13:00,775
Yeah, the shock of discovering
your mind is being invaded by

1176
01:13:00,777 --> 01:13:03,511
an alien life form.

1177
01:13:03,513 --> 01:13:07,315
It conjures up horrible images
of Martian insects knocking

1178
01:13:07,317 --> 01:13:10,051
over the Golden
Gate Bridge.

1179
01:13:10,053 --> 01:13:12,653
But this invasion is
for our benefit, Nick.

1180
01:13:12,655 --> 01:13:17,058
You and I and the others
were chosen by VALIS.

1181
01:13:21,663 --> 01:13:25,066
Will they leave after
Fremont is destroyed?

1182
01:13:25,068 --> 01:13:27,435
If we manage
to destroy him.

1183
01:13:27,437 --> 01:13:29,070
They're our
protectors, Nick.

1184
01:13:29,072 --> 01:13:31,105
They only come when
we need them.

1185
01:13:31,107 --> 01:13:34,142
I had to see
her for myself.

1186
01:13:34,144 --> 01:13:36,811
Has he shown you
pictures of our son?

1187
01:13:36,813 --> 01:13:40,415
I'm so sorry about
this, Mrs. Brady.

1188
01:13:40,417 --> 01:13:41,816
You're going home.

1189
01:13:41,818 --> 01:13:44,519
Come on.

1190
01:13:51,693 --> 01:13:53,528
I need you to go home.

1191
01:13:53,530 --> 01:13:55,630
I'll explain everything to you
later, but you have to trust me.

1192
01:13:55,632 --> 01:13:57,765
What are you doing to us?
I thought we were happy.

1193
01:13:57,767 --> 01:14:00,568
It's not what
you think.

1194
01:14:00,570 --> 01:14:02,036
I don't know,
maybe it's worse.

1195
01:14:02,038 --> 01:14:04,172
Are you in love with her?

1196
01:14:04,174 --> 01:14:07,708
Rachel, you are the only
woman I've ever loved.

1197
01:14:07,710 --> 01:14:09,610
The only woman
I'm ever going to love.

1198
01:14:09,612 --> 01:14:11,446
Then what are
you doing?

1199
01:14:11,448 --> 01:14:13,815
You have to trust me.

1200
01:14:39,641 --> 01:14:41,642
She doesn't understand.

1201
01:14:41,644 --> 01:14:43,644
Did you really
expect her to?

1202
01:14:43,646 --> 01:14:45,446
Do you expect anyone
to understand this?

1203
01:14:45,448 --> 01:14:48,649
I hoped she would.

1204
01:14:48,651 --> 01:14:52,820
My crazy friend Phil
understands, sort of.

1205
01:14:52,822 --> 01:14:54,589
Maybe you
should go home.

1206
01:14:54,591 --> 01:14:57,058
No, this is more
important.

1207
01:14:57,060 --> 01:14:58,759
Are you sure?

1208
01:14:58,761 --> 01:15:02,597
No, I'm not sure.

1209
01:15:02,599 --> 01:15:04,499
But I can't let my son grow up
a world like this if I can do

1210
01:15:04,501 --> 01:15:07,101
something about it.

1211
01:15:08,637 --> 01:15:11,439
Come here.

1212
01:15:18,046 --> 01:15:22,149
The satellite's been up there
for thousands of years.

1213
01:15:22,151 --> 01:15:23,784
What the ancient
Hebrews were to Egypt

1214
01:15:23,786 --> 01:15:25,419
and the early Christians
were to Rome,

1215
01:15:25,421 --> 01:15:28,623
we are now to this corrupt
new American empire.

1216
01:15:28,625 --> 01:15:30,791
It's an ancient
fight, Nick.

1217
01:15:30,793 --> 01:15:32,527
The values of the individual
against the supremacy

1218
01:15:32,529 --> 01:15:34,195
of the state.

1219
01:15:34,197 --> 01:15:35,596
That's why the confession
kits, that's why

1220
01:15:35,598 --> 01:15:37,832
the growing
police supervision.

1221
01:15:37,834 --> 01:15:42,136
Over half the organization has
been discovered and eliminated.

1222
01:15:42,138 --> 01:15:44,171
Aren't you afraid?

1223
01:15:44,173 --> 01:15:47,575
I would be if it weren't
for Fire Bright.

1224
01:15:47,577 --> 01:15:51,178
That's how I refer to the
plasmatic entity within me.

1225
01:15:51,180 --> 01:15:54,148
It's like a little egg of
silver, cold, pale fire,

1226
01:15:54,150 --> 01:15:57,752
glowing with life
just right up here.

1227
01:15:59,588 --> 01:16:07,194
It's strange to have him inside
us, alive, yet unnoticed.

1228
01:16:07,196 --> 01:16:09,497
When we're killed
does he die, too?

1229
01:16:09,499 --> 01:16:12,066
When the body is
destroyed, he leaves.

1230
01:16:12,068 --> 01:16:14,168
But they won't
desert us.

1231
01:16:14,170 --> 01:16:15,836
So just as you and I have
housed and sheltered them,

1232
01:16:15,838 --> 01:16:19,507
they'll take us along with
them into eternity.

1233
01:16:19,509 --> 01:16:21,642
As a reward
for succeeding?

1234
01:16:21,644 --> 01:16:24,645
No, what they value
is the attempt.

1235
01:16:24,647 --> 01:16:27,481
Not the achievement
or the ultimate result.

1236
01:16:27,483 --> 01:16:31,085
They judge us by our intention,
by our hearts.

1237
01:16:42,698 --> 01:16:44,599
This just
in from Moscow.

1238
01:16:44,601 --> 01:16:47,535
Russian authorities report that
an accidental explosion aboard

1239
01:16:47,537 --> 01:16:50,237
the intercept missile launched
to photograph an allegedly

1240
01:16:50,239 --> 01:16:53,074
extra-terrestrial satellite
has destroyed both

1241
01:16:53,076 --> 01:16:55,042
the satellite
and the missile.

1242
01:16:55,044 --> 01:16:57,244
The cause of the
blast is unknown.

1243
01:16:57,246 --> 01:16:58,813
And now,
turning to.....

1244
01:16:58,815 --> 01:17:00,181
Must be a lot of partying
tonight in the Kremlin

1245
01:17:00,183 --> 01:17:01,582
and the White House.

1246
01:17:01,584 --> 01:17:03,718
Well, I'm glad.

1247
01:17:03,720 --> 01:17:06,821
At least it's over
and done with.

1248
01:17:06,823 --> 01:17:08,756
It's not over.

1249
01:17:08,758 --> 01:17:11,659
And it's not
done with.

1250
01:17:15,597 --> 01:17:20,201
With great pleasure I now
authorize Project Coliseum.

1251
01:17:20,203 --> 01:17:22,203
Our toughest laws yet in
the fight against terror

1252
01:17:22,205 --> 01:17:25,706
and subversion.

1253
01:17:43,258 --> 01:17:44,725
Did you see
the news last night?

1254
01:17:44,727 --> 01:17:46,293
Yeah, well, when
you attack a tyranny,

1255
01:17:46,295 --> 01:17:48,362
you've got to expect
it to fight back.

1256
01:17:48,364 --> 01:17:50,131
We knew once they
pinpointed the location

1257
01:17:50,133 --> 01:17:52,233
that they would
destroy it.

1258
01:17:52,235 --> 01:17:54,068
Can another
satellite be sent?

1259
01:17:54,070 --> 01:17:55,736
There's one already on
the way from Albemuth.

1260
01:17:55,738 --> 01:17:57,238
But even traveling
at the speed of light,

1261
01:17:57,240 --> 01:17:59,607
it won't arrive for
hundreds of years.

1262
01:17:59,609 --> 01:18:01,709
That's not going
to do us any good.

1263
01:18:01,711 --> 01:18:03,244
It's hopeless.

1264
01:18:03,246 --> 01:18:06,147
It's not, I've written
down the material.

1265
01:18:06,149 --> 01:18:08,082
What material?
The lyrics.

1266
01:18:08,084 --> 01:18:11,786
Use it on an album you
expect to sell really well.

1267
01:18:11,788 --> 01:18:13,788
What's the message
