talk to Nick Brady
before he died.

1515
01:36:28,850 --> 01:36:30,717
If you want, you can
talk to the Aramchek woman

1516
01:36:30,719 --> 01:36:33,353
he was conspiring with.

1517
01:36:33,355 --> 01:36:35,288
Do you know her?

1518
01:36:35,290 --> 01:36:39,225
No, I never got
to meet her.

1519
01:36:39,227 --> 01:36:42,162
Are you going
to shoot her, too?

1520
01:37:01,382 --> 01:37:02,515
You're Phil.

1521
01:37:02,517 --> 01:37:04,117
Nick's friend, right?

1522
01:37:04,119 --> 01:37:06,286
The science-fiction writer.

1523
01:37:06,288 --> 01:37:07,420
Is he okay?

1524
01:37:07,422 --> 01:37:09,823
No, he isn't.

1525
01:37:09,825 --> 01:37:12,492
They shot him.

1526
01:37:12,494 --> 01:37:15,395
I see.

1527
01:37:16,730 --> 01:37:18,498
And you're sure
it's true.

1528
01:37:18,500 --> 01:37:22,135
They showed
me his body.

1529
01:37:24,839 --> 01:37:27,407
I suppose I'm next.

1530
01:37:29,410 --> 01:37:32,412
No trial,
no investigation.

1531
01:37:32,414 --> 01:37:34,280
They're really
afraid of us.

1532
01:37:34,282 --> 01:37:37,417
That's right.

1533
01:37:37,419 --> 01:37:40,320
I don't think
they'll kill you.

1534
01:37:40,322 --> 01:37:41,621
They said they want
you to write crappy novels

1535
01:37:41,623 --> 01:37:45,058
for them full of
pro-government propaganda.

1536
01:37:45,060 --> 01:37:47,293
The books are
already written.

1537
01:37:47,295 --> 01:37:49,095
It'll just be my
name on them.

1538
01:37:49,097 --> 01:37:50,797
That's good.

1539
01:37:50,799 --> 01:37:52,765
It means they
don't trust you.

1540
01:37:52,767 --> 01:37:55,768
It's when they trust
you that it's bad.

1541
01:37:55,770 --> 01:37:59,339
It's the next worst thing
to being on their side.

1542
01:37:59,341 --> 01:38:02,275
I'm sorry for all this.

1543
01:38:03,811 --> 01:38:05,545
For what Nick
got you into.

1544
01:38:05,547 --> 01:38:08,481
It's okay.

1545
01:38:08,483 --> 01:38:10,817
We're immortal.

1546
01:38:10,819 --> 01:38:14,420
VALIS conferred that on us, and
it will on everyone, someday.

1547
01:38:14,422 --> 01:38:17,190
I don't feel
too bad, though.

1548
01:38:17,192 --> 01:38:20,193
I feel like we put
up a good fight.

1549
01:38:21,462 --> 01:38:24,397
Time's up.

1550
01:38:42,316 --> 01:38:45,184
Don't tell them how
lousy their novels are.

1551
01:38:45,186 --> 01:38:47,520
Let them find out
the hard way.

1552
01:38:54,495 --> 01:38:57,563
So that's how
it all came down.

1553
01:38:57,565 --> 01:38:58,831
My friend Nicholas Brady
had tried

1554
01:38:58,833 --> 01:39:02,502
to save the
world and failed.

1555
01:39:02,504 --> 01:39:06,339
And I found myself
in this place.

1556
01:39:06,341 --> 01:39:08,808
The dark night
of the soul.

1557
01:39:08,810 --> 01:39:11,511
Alone and forgotten.

1558
01:39:11,513 --> 01:39:14,480
Scribbling furtively
on scraps of paper

1559
01:39:14,482 --> 01:39:17,550
that no one would ever
get a chance to read.

1560
01:39:28,796 --> 01:39:31,831
So you used to
be a writer?

1561
01:39:31,833 --> 01:39:34,233
Yeah.

1562
01:39:36,503 --> 01:39:38,538
In a way, I still am.

1563
01:39:38,540 --> 01:39:43,443
Were you a member
of Aramchek?

1564
01:39:43,445 --> 01:39:45,345
No.

1565
01:39:45,347 --> 01:39:47,280
Know anything
about it?

1566
01:39:47,282 --> 01:39:49,549
Some friends
of mine belonged.

1567
01:39:49,551 --> 01:39:52,218
Dead?

1568
01:39:52,220 --> 01:39:54,554
Yeah.

1569
01:39:54,556 --> 01:39:56,456
So, what's
Aramchek teach?

1570
01:39:56,458 --> 01:39:59,559
Are they really diehard
communists?

1571
01:39:59,561 --> 01:40:01,561
No.

1572
01:40:01,563 --> 01:40:05,331
They think we shouldn't put
our faith in any human rulers.

1573
01:40:05,333 --> 01:40:08,401
That there's a vast intelligence
above the stars, that guides us,

1574
01:40:08,403 --> 01:40:11,537
that's interested
in our welfare.

1575
01:40:11,539 --> 01:40:14,841
That sounds like
a religious idea.

1576
01:40:14,843 --> 01:40:19,145
I always thought Aramchek was
a revolutionary organization.

1577
01:40:19,147 --> 01:40:20,713
It's both.

1578
01:40:20,715 --> 01:40:24,484
A subversive organization guided
by a supreme higher power.

1579
01:40:28,088 --> 01:40:29,422
They think our loyalty
should be to the values

1580
01:40:29,424 --> 01:40:32,458
of that higher
entity alone.

1581
01:40:32,460 --> 01:40:34,560
You believe that, too?

1582
01:40:34,562 --> 01:40:37,497
I didn't at first.

1583
01:40:37,499 --> 01:40:41,067
But now, maybe.

1584
01:40:41,069 --> 01:40:43,369
So this, supreme being,
does it tell

1585
01:40:43,371 --> 01:40:46,406
the Aramchek
people what to do?

1586
01:40:46,408 --> 01:40:48,408
They called it VALIS.

1587
01:40:48,410 --> 01:40:52,211
It spoke to them
in visions.

1588
01:40:52,213 --> 01:40:55,081
And will again, someday,
I believe that.

1589
01:40:56,316 --> 01:40:58,351
You're a strange guy.

1590
01:40:58,353 --> 01:40:59,719
You ever hear
its voice?

1591
01:40:59,721 --> 01:41:02,588
No.

1592
01:41:02,590 --> 01:41:05,425
But I wish I had.

1593
01:41:19,473 --> 01:41:23,242
I've still got my printing
supplies hidden away.

1594
01:41:23,244 --> 01:41:25,244
I might be able to
run off some literature

1595
01:41:25,246 --> 01:41:27,613
for you and your
Aramchek friends.

1596
01:41:27,615 --> 01:41:30,450
You interested?

1597
01:41:30,452 --> 01:41:33,586
Yeah, very much.

1598
01:41:33,588 --> 01:41:36,622
First, I've got to get back
to my friend's wife and son,

1599
01:41:36,624 --> 01:41:40,493
make sure they're okay.

1600
01:41:40,495 --> 01:41:43,329
You think Aramchek
would take me?

1601
01:41:43,331 --> 01:41:45,631
I need help, I can't
get anywhere alone.

1602
01:41:45,633 --> 01:41:48,301
Sure.

1603
01:41:48,303 --> 01:41:51,270
Maybe they
have already.

1604
01:41:51,272 --> 01:41:53,639
I've never heard
any voices.

1605
01:41:53,641 --> 01:41:56,642
Your own voice
might be the voice.

1606
01:41:58,679 --> 01:42:02,315
How about that?

1607
01:42:02,317 --> 01:42:05,218
Nobody's ever said
that to me before.

1608
01:42:10,657 --> 01:42:12,692
You think believing
about a heavenly power

1609
01:42:12,694 --> 01:42:14,627
get them anywhere?

1610
01:42:14,629 --> 01:42:16,596
Not in this world.

1611
01:42:16,598 --> 01:42:19,665
I've got to tell you something
you maybe don't want to hear.

1612
01:42:19,667 --> 01:42:21,634
I know you loved your friends
and maybe they are happy spirits

1613
01:42:21,636 --> 01:42:23,669
somewhere up in the sky,

1614
01:42:23,671 --> 01:42:27,306
but even if they are,
that's not good enough.

1615
01:42:27,308 --> 01:42:29,342
They gave their lives
for that belief.

1616
01:42:29,344 --> 01:42:32,211
What I'm saying is, it's got
to be something here first.

1617
01:42:33,814 --> 01:42:39,652
This is where the suffering is,
this is where the injustice is.

1618
01:42:39,654 --> 01:42:41,721
This Valis or God or whatever
you want to call it,

1619
01:42:41,723 --> 01:42:44,457
has to do something
for us here.

1620
01:42:44,459 --> 01:42:47,360
Or what the
fuck good is it?

1621
01:42:54,568 --> 01:42:56,536
What's this I heard about
the Aramchek people having

1622
01:42:56,538 --> 01:43:00,339
a beautiful silver egg placed
in each of their foreheads?

1623
01:43:00,341 --> 01:43:02,208
That's what
they believe.

1624
01:43:02,210 --> 01:43:04,677
My theory is it enters along the
optic nerve to the pineal gland

1625
01:43:04,679 --> 01:43:07,680
by means of radiation beamed
down by the satellite.

1626
01:43:07,682 --> 01:43:09,749
The egg hatches when they die
and incorporates them into

1627
01:43:09,751 --> 01:43:13,753
the vast living entity
in the stratosphere.

1628
01:43:17,691 --> 01:43:19,592
I got a confession
to make.

1629
01:43:19,594 --> 01:43:22,361
I know a little more about
Aramchek than I admitted.

1630
01:43:22,363 --> 01:43:24,597
I used to be a preacher.

1631
01:43:24,599 --> 01:43:26,732
The beautiful silver egg
that guarantees immortality,

1632
01:43:26,734 --> 01:43:28,501
that's in
the Bible, Phil.

1633
01:43:28,503 --> 01:43:31,437
Jesus speaks about
it several times.

1634
01:43:31,439 --> 01:43:34,207
The real meaning was known
only to his disciples.

1635
01:43:34,209 --> 01:43:36,342
But now it's
coming back.

1636
01:43:36,344 --> 01:43:37,543
Tell me more,
preacher.

1637
01:43:37,545 --> 01:43:39,378
I'm not
a preacher anymore.

1638
01:43:39,380 --> 01:43:40,780
Religion is shit.

1639
01:43:40,782 --> 01:43:43,382
It's more honest work
being a plumber.

1640
01:43:43,384 --> 01:43:45,451
You believe what my friend said
is true and yet you still--

1641
01:43:45,453 --> 01:43:50,323
I still say the work has
to be done here on earth.

1642
01:43:50,325 --> 01:43:53,726
Let me ask you this--
where did Jesus do his work?

1643
01:43:53,728 --> 01:43:56,729
Where did he teach?

1644
01:43:58,799 --> 01:44:00,566
Hey, boss.

1645
01:44:00,568 --> 01:44:04,303
Can we take five?
It's hot out here.

1646
01:44:20,287 --> 01:44:22,755
Look at those kids
watching us.

1647
01:44:33,567 --> 01:44:36,469
♪ Want fun? ♪

1648
01:44:36,471 --> 01:44:37,503
♪ I know you
need some... ♪

1649
01:44:37,505 --> 01:44:39,338
That's it.

1650
01:44:39,340 --> 01:44:40,506
That's the song!

1651
01:44:40,508 --> 01:44:41,774
What?

1652
01:44:41,776 --> 01:44:44,410
That's the song!

1653
01:44:44,412 --> 01:44:46,712
Hey, it's cool,
he's not going anywhere.

1654
01:44:46,714 --> 01:44:50,449
I'll keep an
eye on him.

1655
01:44:50,451 --> 01:44:52,752
♪ Wasted ♪

1656
01:44:52,754 --> 01:44:55,788
♪ But kept in
God's graces ♪

1657
01:44:55,790 --> 01:45:01,060
They must have gotten another
record company to press it--

1658
01:45:01,062 --> 01:45:04,330
while Progressive was preparing
its version, other members of

1659
01:45:04,332 --> 01:45:08,334
Aramchek must have been
working on the song, too.

1660
01:45:08,336 --> 01:45:09,635
They made it.

1661
01:45:09,637 --> 01:45:11,504
It's out.

1662
01:45:11,506 --> 01:45:13,806
Do you know
what this means?

1663
01:45:13,808 --> 01:45:16,108
I never listen to that
rock and roll junk.

1664
01:45:16,110 --> 01:45:17,543
I used to have
a big record collection,

1665
01:45:17,545 --> 01:45:20,346
mostly classical
and jazz.

1666
01:45:20,348 --> 01:45:23,783
As far as I'm concerned, that
music's just for the kids.

1667
01:45:23,785 --> 01:45:25,685
Yeah.

1668
01:45:25,687 --> 01:45:28,654
That's right,
for the kids.

1669
01:45:28,656 --> 01:45:32,191
The music's for them.

1670
01:45:33,760 --> 01:45:37,330
I guess it's gonna
be up to them now.

1671
01:45:47,542 --> 01:45:50,409
While we waited to finish our
sentences, I continued to work

1672
01:45:50,411 --> 01:45:54,413
on Nick's story, which turned
out to be my story, too.

1673
01:45:56,850 --> 01:45:59,852
I wanted to chronicle the
origins of that faint flicker

1674
01:45:59,854 --> 01:46:03,723
of hope that would someday
burn out a cancerous regime,

1675
01:46:03,725 --> 01:46:06,092
the humble beginnings of a mass
movement of young people that

1676
01:46:06,094 --> 01:46:10,463
would eventually change
our country for the better.

1677
01:46:10,465 --> 01:46:13,666
Even if they found my
manuscript and destroyed it,

1678
01:46:13,668 --> 01:46:17,470
I would still have been the
first to bear witness.

1679
01:46:21,641 --> 01:46:24,777
I had faith that
I would not be the last.

1680
01:47:44,090 --> 01:47:48,127
♪ We have no wings ♪

1681
01:47:49,196 --> 01:47:53,566
♪ We are not angels ♪

1682
01:47:54,768 --> 01:47:57,603
♪ Just flesh and blood ♪

1683
01:47:59,639 --> 01:48:03,609
♪ In skin and in bone ♪

1684
01:48:05,512 --> 01:48:10,115
♪ Born from the ruin ♪

1685
01:48:11,117 --> 01:48:16,222
♪ Like other mammals ♪

1686
01:48:16,224 --> 01:48:19,592
♪ Over the earth ♪

1687
01:48:21,161 --> 01:48:24,663
♪ We swarm and we roam ♪

1688
01:48:28,101 --> 01:48:30,603
♪ We walk around ♪

1689
01:48:30,605 --> 01:48:33,472
♪ We don't know why ♪

1690
01:48:33,474 --> 01:48:36,141
♪ Above the ground ♪

1691
01:48:36,143 --> 01:48:39,144
♪ Beneath the sky ♪

1692
01:48:40,514 --> 01:48:45,651
♪ And I declare
that we are free ♪

1693
01:48:45,653 --> 01:48:51,557
♪ And we are equal
in our liberty ♪

1694
01:48:51,559 --> 01:48:56,095
♪ And I declare
that we are free ♪

1695
01:48:56,097 --> 01:49:02,167
♪ And we are equal
in our destiny ♪

1696
01:49:09,809 --> 01:49:13,512
♪ We are not slaves ♪

1697
01:49:14,814 --> 01:49:19,685
♪ Not to be tortured ♪

1698
01:49:19,687 --> 01:49:24,690
♪ To be abused ♪

1699
01:49:24,692 --> 01:49:30,696
♪ By the hand
with the gun ♪

1700
01:49:30,698 --> 01:49:33,699
♪ We're all born free ♪

1701
01:49:35,702 --> 01:49:41,206
♪ We're all born equal ♪

1702
01:49:41,208 --> 01:49:45,844
♪ All though the night ♪

1703
01:49:45,846 --> 01:49:49,582
♪ And out in the sun ♪

1704
01:49:52,852 --> 01:49:55,154
♪ When we arrive ♪

1705
01:49:55,156 --> 01:49:58,090
♪ Until we die ♪

1706
01:49:58,092 --> 01:50:05,230
♪ We are alive
beneath the sky ♪

1707
01:50:05,232 --> 01:50:10,069
♪ And I declare that
we are free ♪

1708
01:50:10,071 --> 01:50:16,241
♪ And we are equal
in our dignity ♪

1709
01:50:16,243 --> 01:50:20,613
♪ I declare that
we are free ♪

1710
01:50:20,615 --> 01:50:26,852
♪ And we are equal
in our destiny ♪

1711
01:50:29,356 --> 01:50:32,358
♪ To be ♪

1712
01:50:34,728 --> 01:50:37,730
♪ To be ♪

1713
01:50:40,700 --> 01:50:43,302
♪ Human ♪

1714
01:50:48,241 --> 01:50:50,743
♪ To be ♪

1715
01:50:50,745 --> 01:50:54,213
♪ To be ♪

1716
01:50:54,215 --> 01:51:00,285
♪ Human ♪

